Class Common.Events

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.penthera.virtuososdk.Common.Events
  • Enclosing class:
    Common
    public static final class Common.Events extends java.lang.Object
    Identifies Virtuoso's Events, meaning "things that gets reported to the Backplane." Provides helper methods for instantiating Events that Virtuoso reports.

      addCustomEvent 
      static boolean addCustomEvent(Context context, java.lang.String aName, java.lang.String assetId, long data)
      Creates and automatically saves a Custom Event using the provided Context.
      public static boolean addCustomEvent(Context context, java.lang.String aName, java.lang.String assetId, long data)
      Creates and automatically saves a Custom Event using the provided Context. The Custom Event allows you to create arbitrarily named events and record these events on the Backplane along with the Virtuoso built-in events. This method version takes a long data argument. To send text event data, use the customEvent method.
      Parameters:
      context - Context to use when saving the event
      aName - Name for this custom Event
      assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
      data - Data to be associated with this Event
      Returns:
      True if the event was successfully saved

The Custom Event allows you to create arbitrarily named events and record these events on the Backplane along with the Virtuoso built-in events. This method version takes a String data argument.       addPlayStartEvent

      public static boolean addPlayStartEvent(Context context, java.lang.String assetId, java.lang.String assetUuid)
      Creates and automatically saves a Play-Start Event using the provided Context. Include asset Uuid if the asset has been added for download to ensure correct management of expiry. It is optional to allow for recording streaming events.
      Parameters:
      context - Context to use when saving the event
      assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
      assetUuid - System generated ID for the asset
      Returns:
      True if the event was successfully saved
